10:
Ah! You two startled me. I was just
looking for a quest, but... 
*sigh* I don't think I could handle 
any of these myself.
15:
In need of work, huh? You did
mention that you were planning a
Halloween party for the kids.
19:
Exactly. See, the other kids'
Halloween costumes get fancier by
the year.
21:
It wasn't easy, but I managed to get
everyone at the orphanage
something fun for the big day.
24:
That explains why you're dressed up
like an angel. It does suit you,
though.
28:
Ahaha, thank you. The kids picked it
out for me. They even made the
wings themselves!
33:
They did?! They're so detailed, I
almost thought those were real—
36:
Hang on... ARE those real feathers?
How much did that cost?
41:
N-no, wait, I can explain! They tried
to make them out of paper, but they
kept falling apart, and then one of
the kids started crying and, and—
44:
I, um, caved in and helped make a
new pair...
51:
Which means you need to earn
enough FOR the party.
55:
The gold's already spent, so looks
like we'll just have to hit the quests.
Were there any good ones for a
party of three?
59:
We'll figure something out, Corinna.
It would be a shame to let the
costumes go to waste.
63:
Oh goodness! Th-thank you both so
much! I promise, I WILL make it up to
you!
69:
Not gonna lie, when the client said
we'd be "tidying up" their mansion, 
I wasn't expecting... this.
72:
Looks like we've got our work cut out
for us.
76:
I'm starting to see why the townsfolk
call the estate "haunted."
81:
*yelp* Wh-what was that?! ...This
place isn't r-REALLY haunted, is it?
86:
Hey! Whoever's out there, come out
and show yourself!
91:
We were just messing around,
honest! Heh, what do you think of
our secret base?
93:
Your secret base? It seems we've
found the source of the rumors, then.
96:
S-Stars above, you had me going
there. N-not that I was SCARED or
anything, nope! Not me! Ahaha... ha...
103:
Huh?! I think we might have a REAL
ghost on our hands!
106:
A poltergeist. Corinna, we'll take the
ghost. Watch the kids!
115: Shhh, everything's going to be fine.
120:
Stars, shine forth—and deliver unto
this lost soul your Guidance!
130:
I-I know you said you'd handle it, 
so I hope that was okay...
134:
Of course. You went above and
beyond, Corinna.
...And took half of the room with you.
143:
I'd understand docking some pay to
cover the repairs, but to refuse to
pay at all... *sigh*
148: I'm so sorry... This is all my fault.
152:
Good evening. I heard all about your
heroics from the Guild. I'm terribly
sorry my kids caused you trouble,
and am eternally grateful that you
saved them.
154:
H-heroics? I hardly did anything,
really. I'm just glad they're safe.
156:
No need to be shy! I don't know how
I could ever repay you—but please
accept a donation to your
orphanage as a small token of my
appreciation.
160:
Huh?! N-no, this is far too much! 
I couldn't possibly accept this...
162:
I thought it only fitting to help the
children in your care as thanks for
helping mine. I hope they have a
positively bewitching Halloween!
164:
I wouldn't want to disturb you this
late in the evening, so I'll swing by
the orphanage in the morning to
finalize the payment. Again, I cannot
thank you enough.
166:
No, thank YOU! This is all very
generous!
171: All's well that ends well, huh?
176:
You can say that again! I can't wait
to get everything ready for the party!
